    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>LEAD: The Capitol Steps, a singing group that specializes in political satire, has just released its Christmas album: ''Ronald the Red-Faced Reagan.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>LEAD: The Capitol Steps, a singing group that specializes in political satire, has just released its Christmas album: ''Ronald the Red-Faced Reagan.''</p>
        <p>The Capitol Steps, a singing group that specializes in political satire, has just released its Christmas album: ''Ronald the Red-Faced Reagan.''</p>
        <p>The 19 tunes cover subjects ranging from Gary Hart to the ozone layer. ''O Little Town of Washington'' begins this way:</p>
        <p>O little town of Washington  How come your people lie?  The papers say  The C.I.A.  is first to falsify</p>
        <p>''Here Come Democrats,'' set to ''Here Comes Santa Claus,'' goes:</p>
        <p>Here come Democrats  Here comes Santa Claus  Giving money away  Big entitlements  Lots of bureaucrats  Eating money like hay</p>
        <p>The title song, from a ditty about a reindeer, includes this lyric:</p>
        <p>Then one day in Contragate  Reagan came to say  Someone here must be contrite  Take the blame for me tonight  After the staff stopped shakin'  They decided that henceforth  Every mistake by Reagan  They would blame on Ollie North.</p>
        <p>WASHINGTON TALK: BRIEFING</p>
      </block>
